caption: I’ve been to dak probably about 15 times since i discovered it and literally every time it just smacks. i’ve tried their wings, rice bowls, fries, and more and i can guarantee that anything you get from their menu will be 9 or 10/10. Also, the people working there are some of the sweetest, most compliant people i’ve seen in a restaurant. Hard shoutout to Dak and I hope you give it a try cuz you shan’t regret it.

The food is good but it’s wayyyyyy to expensive. I can’t eat here and not think about how small the portions are and how much I paid. I wish it was less expensive or the portions were bigger because I love Korean food.

The food is always fresh and delicious. The son has a heart of gold and humility and is always appreciative of the customers who patronize their business. He loves and respects his parents for the sweat equity they've put in the business for him.
Good food and quality ingredients!
I know this food is good even though this was my first time. Wings need a solid 2 more minutes, or the heat turned up. I was a fry cook once. I'll be back in the future to double check this one.

Really loving the food but the entire ordering process needs a serious overhaul. I’ve called before to order and nobody has picked up. Wait times for food can be an hour plus.  I understand that precautions have to be taken but I don’t see how that affects some of the timing issues their having.
rude staff
rude lady staff frount counter

Great wings and bowls! I admit it's a bit pricy but the flavors are unmatched! Great local family run spot for take out! Never had a bad experience here and have always been pleased with the food. I recommend getting some extra sauce on the side  if you get the wings!
The wings and rice bowls are amazing! Love this place. Never disappoints :)

Ordered both flavors of the wings and they were both delicious. The wings were huge, I ate about 3 and was full. I wish we ordered some rice to go with the wings but now we know for next time haha. We also ordered some waffle fries as well and those were some of the best waffle fries I've ever had. They were fresh and crispy but still full if potato. Some places are mostly just potato skin, but not this place.
Amazing wings and super safe setup for pick ups
Great place for wings, must try !
Very unpleasant & unorganized!
The biggest wings I've ever eaten.  Try both sauces with your wings.

Wow! On a Saturday night at 5pm the wait was 2 hours long. You know what......It was well worth it. First you have to write you name on the easier board and wait to be called. The guy that calls names, whispers names out to listen carefully.
I’d like to argue that Dak wings are the best wings in Chicago. Absolutely delicious and extremely filling. The Korean flavor is my go to.
Some of the biggest wings I've ever had!
Best wings in Chicago hands down. They give you not just the tiny part of the wing, but the whole thing! Their moo kimchi is also delicious.

Dak easily has the best chicken wings I've ever had.  And possibly the best chicken I've ever had.  There are some famous fried chicken places in NOLA that I'd have to do a side by side comparison.  I highly recommend getting the sauce on the side to keep the skin crunchy, especially if you're ordering out.
The service is always rapid, good mood, super nice staff members. I will visit again when I get nearby.

We LOVE this place. Been going here since they opened over 8 years ago. Doing just take out now, but it's still awesome. Rice bowl's rock as do the waffle fries and Duk Boki. Daniel is a great owner and great addition to the hood
Wings are fantastic
The wings at Dak will change your life. Order them in the Dak sauce.
Best dokbukki ever❤️❤️❤️❤️ The guy was super nice and cool. Definitely come again 1000times

Beat chicken spot in westborough as theyre not to many chicken spots in the area or hardly any. Theyre good at seating you on time the staff is great friendly and kind ive been going here for the past year i like it the only con is they change their menu. It used to be any order of wings with "1 additional sides of your choice" now they only give raddish or salad witch will be an additional cost for any other sides but this still the beat place for chicken

The chicken wings were dry, over cooked and greasy, the garlic soy sauce was too watery and salty. Dak Chicken was very bland and a lot of rice. Feels like it was missing something.  The waffle fries were flabby, greasy and mushy in texture

I love this restaurant! They serve great food, their menu is decent, The cook in that restaurant is very trained, I like a lot trying all their food. The food is consistently fresh and tasty, the service towards the guests  is nice. I often go to  this place and I was never discontended.  I highly recommend it.

Outstanding. Of course they're most well-known for their chicken wings, but their rice bowls are absolutely fantastic too. Dak never disappoints. I can't give them my business right now because of Corona, so the most I can do is write this well-deserved review.
This is one of our favorite neighborhood places. The people are awesome, the food is great, and they truly appreciate their customers. Great place👍
Delicious wings and wonderful owners!

Absolutely fantastic, Stopped by with  my  family for an early lunch while in Chicago  this week. Had a wonderful  chat with the owners which was  a  true  pleasure.  We shared some wings and rice bowls, French fries and pickled radishes. Incredible lunch. We all agreed Dak is our new favorite place in Chicago.
The food is good but the meat portions in the rice bowls are small. Bulgogi besf is really good. Chickens wings are ok, just a little greasy.

We chose this place solely because of the proximity to where we were at the moment. The guy taking our order seemed to have a bit of an attitude so we just ordered quickly and didn't want to bother him with any further questions.
Delicious, and the crispiness held up the next day!
Love the wings, they are addictive. But my fave is spicy pork bowl!

I'm surprised I haven't reviewed this before. I lived in Korea for a number of years and this is my favorite place for Korean chicken wings.  They have super crispy skin, perfectly seasoned, and super moist on the inside. They aren't as saucy as some other Korean chicken places, but that's one reason why I like them. They have just enough but avoid being drowned in sauce, though I'm sure you could ask them for extra if you like that style.  For the price, size and quality, this is an excellent place.

(Translated by Google) It's alright. Not great not bad but a good take on Korean chicken. The frying was spot on and probably the best fry compared to other Korean chicken places is Chicagoland but not really the traditional Korean style yangnyum chicken. Having it being less sweeter and not as sticky is an American take. The dduckbokki was interesting as well. Still all in all a good place. It's good to eat but you can eat it if you think it's Korean. Biting really too little. Less than 2 pieces per chicken ...  (Original) It's alright. Not great not bad but a good take on Korean chicken. The frying was spot on and probably the best fry compared to other Korean chicken places is Chicagoland but not really the traditional Korean style yangnyum chicken. Having it being less sweeter and not as sticky is an American take. The dduckbokki was interesting as well. Still all in all a good place. 먹을만 하지만 한국식이라 생각히면 실밍하실 수 있음. 무는 정말 너무 적게 줌. 치킨 한조각당 2개도 안됨...
This is high-quality Korean fried chicken; get it Dak style! So tasty!
Good Korean BBQ, but I thought the spicey chicken bowl was fantastic.
Awesome
Great wings. Wings are the biggest I've ever seen
Finest food, very kind staff members, always fantastic vibes. They charge affordable pricing and the food quality is great. Great work.
Terrible quality Food is tasteless Below average Very over priced Never again
Delicious wings and bowls
So much fun so damn good. The only difficulty I had eating it was my wide goofy smile.
G00d
Love this place, I even moved closer to this restaurant, I know it’s sounds funny but it’s true lol
Great customer service, tasty food all served in a timely manner!!!
These wings are delicious but over priced. Five whole wings for almost 12 bucks.  French fries cost 4 bucks & you can serve yourself some water from the tin on the counter.
Dak's classic Korean BBQ made with delicious sauces and meats!
5 wings is definitely enough for one person
Nice pterodactyl wings!!
The fried jumbo chicken wings is just amazing, crispy outside, juicy inside. I chose the Dak glaze, with soy sauce, honey and ginger. So good!

The restaurant is clean the air is pure and the food most flavorful. the chicken wings are brined and you'll notice a hint of Ginger in each crisp delectable bite. Kimchi is made on site as well as the private recipe egg rolls. The signature Dak sauce is a must have.
Love the chicken size of wings, NOT all consistent in size of wings. Some were smaller portions not as big as I was told.

I ordered 15 wings not thinking it meant 15 whole wings. Best mistake. Imagine your best Chinese chicken wing that's been marinated in ginger/green onion/lemon/garlic/etc fried perfectly and now add a Korean sweet and spicy sauce to it. It's too much flavor for a chicken wing.

💯 Amazing wings and simple, streamlined menu. Go for the wings and get the wings. They are legendary. Everything else is fine but get the wings. Dak sauce is best. Did I mention that you should get the wings? Dak wings best wings!
Well made, small selection of Korean fare.  Many come for the Korean style hot wings.

My girlfriend and me both like the chicken wings there and their rib tips are real good too hopefully we will enjoy more than menu we both have low vision while I have low vision she has none she's total so when we get to menu and get it red we will order more stuff from there but so far everything we've had has been very good and tasty and customer service is great
right off the red, underappreciated wing joint
The spicy wings are so delicious. You get five, and they are huge! They offer a good selection of bowls, as well.
Consistently on point!
Different 👌
Great chicken! A little sweet though.
Back to the place after 1 year. Their Dak sauce chicken wings are still so good. Loved it!
They lost my order and for some reason called me to see if I grabbed it when I ordered Uber eats? Beyond that mix up honestly just go bop n grill it's better.
Awesome Korean style wings!!
Excellent Korean fried chicken! Very casual dining, but excellent food. Would absolutely recommend.
Go for Spicy bbq wings.

Extremely loud to dine in, wings & egg rolls are unpleasant, the taste is hot & spice but unappealing to me. I did not like the potato salad at all, small portions for price - I couldn't finish the food.

This is literally my favorite place in the city. When I'm sad, their food cheers me up. When I'm happy I come here to celebrate. I've tried many different bulgogi places in the city and this is by far the freshest, highest quality, and most unique. If I ever get married I've literally thought of asking them to cater... idk if they actually would but I literally dream of the flavors at this place when Im not there. I love this place so damn much! Oh yeah, and their chicken wings are huge and moist and the skin is perfectly done with the best tasting sauce I've ever had on chicken. I literally jump around my apartment dancing, singing "Dak, Dak, Chickenhead!" Because this food literally gives me the lifeblood energy to survive this cruel world.
Dak closes at 9pm but if you call them at 8: 40  they are almost always out of wings .
Good place to eat Korean fast food. Tastes good.
Love this place! So good! The Carrot fries never disappoint. I eat here almost once a week and it is consistently good.
Giant wings that are spectacular, the spicy pork bowl is equally as great. Wish I were a cow and had more stomachs to devour this deliciousness.
Amazing flavors and crispy wings, great service!
The best service and the best food! Everything is always fresh and delicious!
I love Dak. Great wings and rice bowls full of veggies. Plus the Korean drinks and chips are so fun!
Today was my husband and I first time eating at dak and we really enjoyed it. The wings were cooked perfectly and the sauces are DELICIOUS.

A VERY CLEAN ALTHOUGH A LITTLE UPSCALE VARIETY OF KOREAN CHICKEN WINGS...HUGE WINGS 6 FOR 10$...CUSTOM MADE...WAIT IS USUALLY 10 MINUTES OR MORE....BETTER THAN WINGSTOP OR OTHER LARGE CHAIN RESTAURANTS...IN LIÑCOLN PARK THIS BUSINESS WOULD BOOM.
I love this place. The food is absolutely delicious 😋. A must try.

Great Korean style wings and rice bowls.  Friendly service.  A gem in Edgewater.  Glad it's here.  Love the spicy pork and bulgogi bowls.  Wings are sweet and/or spicy and always crispy yet not battered.  Each wing is the whole 3 pc. wing so when you order 5 you actually get 15 wing pieces.  Totally worth it.

In my opinion, the way a restaurant handles a problem makes it stand out.  We've been long-time fans of Dak but recently had an issue with an order.  Without question, the staff was kind enough to remedy the situation. We got to enjoy our meal and we will be customers for life because they truly care about its customers.

Some of the largest chicken wings I have ever seen or tasted...everything is made to your specifications so it is fresh...the salad meals are healthy...loved them the wait is ten minutes no matter what you order...tasty and nutritional...

I got some wings with the dak sauce which were good bits not outstanding. Compared to other wings I have tried, I definitely think they are competitive in terms of size, flavor, originality, and quality. I was super full after eating three wings and their kimchi (which was delicious).

Huge steroid infused Jumbo wings. Zero crispiness. Dak Sauce? Soy & Garlic. Weird texture,terrible flavor and aftertaste. Minimalist dining room, and dull. This place is hype. Korean chain Bonchon blows them away.
Challenge you to find something that's not delish!
Great taste! Good size wings, can never finish the 5 wings
Jumbo wings are very good. Usually a wait
Small place. There are many options that it's hard to say which is better. Also a wide range of fancy hot sauces. Staff is fast and attentive.
The wings are huge! Wish I had gone with a friend...5 wings and fries was a huge meal for just me. Dipping the fries in the leftover Dak sauce was a savory delight.
(Translated by Google) Ok, it’s a bit tired.  (Original) 还行 有点腻
The chicken wings are great!!!
I'm in this place way too often.  Definitely a favorite.
Cozy restaurant with amazing Korean inspired fried chicken. A must if you love umami flavors paired with deliciously, crispy chicken.
Waffle fries are so good
Very good with wings.  It's a smart place. I usually get mine to go. Solid food.
Wings were soooooooo good! Also, the young lady who worked there was delightful. Will be coming back soon!
The spicy wings are incredible here!  5 wings is definitely enough (I mean, there's never ENOUGH, but you'll be satisfied for sure).

Listen here, dont believe all these paid reviews. The flavorless, pigeon meat wings aint whats happening. My friend Nick suggested this place - we aint friends no more. Just talked to American Express -this a fraudulent purchase. Take your money to Lil Ceasars you gonna be happier. Also, edgewater a super giechi area jo.

Have been wanting to try this spot for wings for months. After a long bike ride, my nephew and I stopped in and kept it simple by ordering spicy wings and a small waffle 🍟. Oh man, they did not disappoint.  The wings were huge, crispy and super flavorful; the best I've ever had in Chicago to date. We were both full with just thw wings and order of fries. The owner sat and talked to us for a bit. Super friendly guy. I will definitely be back soon. Sal just earned its place as my favorite Korean Bbbq wing spot.
The best thing to come from online dating so far. Phenomenal wings and rice bowls. Get the waffle fries to soak up the extra wing sauce too!

This place has some of the best friend chicken in the city. Today I had a very stressful day and ended up just getting the bulgogi bi bim bop and it was very comforting after the day I had.  I forgot to take a picture because I was so hungry so I took a pic of my empty bowl... Nothing says good food like a clean plate right?  It has been a much welcome addition to the neighborhood.
Wings and waffle fries. Every time. Can't go wrong.
I had one of the bowls.  I want to go back and try the wings and fries.  It was really good.
I come here for the best wings, they are really huge! kinda Dragon's wings kinda thing
Been a loyal customer of this joint for 4 years because I go to Loyola. Unfortunately, this place has slipped badly. $13 for a bowl of rice which its quantity is a joke. Literally two bites.

Giant Korean style chicken wings with good selection of sides. Unfortunately the flavors were off on the day we visited, and everything was very very salty. There were also no air conditioning for eating in. The wings are expensive (10/$19), but they are the whole wing instead of just the drum. The dukbokki is deep fried and served with beef. Free or metered street parking, indoor seating, take out, the person who was working seemed disgruntled and annoyed, maybe due to the hot weather.
good chicken wings
Giant kick ass wings and real nice people.

Small joint and Pricey! Bulgogi is okay (dish with marinaded meat and veggies on top of white rice. Unfortunately, wings are pretty good. Literally, need to cut down on price !!! 5 wings are $10. Seriously.
Healthy and tasty. Win!

My husband says this place has some of the best wings he’s ever had. I get the tofu bowls, they are amazing. This place has a sign outside that says no outside beverages, but we asked and it is actually BYOB!

This is my favorite fried chicken restaurant in Chicago. The staff are very friendly and the Dak fried chicken is delicious. I hope they open more branches in Chicago as the current location is far from mine.
The bibimbop was delicious! And there spicy bbq wings were tasty!
Great wings!
I love this place! Wings are to die for!!!! It's always a bit of a wait, because it's made on the spot. Definitely recommend to come here!
OMG best wings ever and the waffle fries
Good Wings
Tasty

Place is amazing.  Not a huge menu but everything they do there is outstanding.  You can't go wrong with anything on the menu.  I tried their rice bowls and chicken wings and all were amazing.  Went there couple of times with few different folks and clients and they all loved it.  Only bad thing I can think of is parking...  you have to pay and sometimes you have to walk a block or three.  Also, place is not big so no huge groups.

Super great place right off the L stop. The best Korean fried chicken in the city! The wings are full wings (drumette, wingette, and tip) , so you get a lot for the price. They only sell a limited amount of wings per day, so don't get there too late! Also highly recommend the dukbokki...the rice cakes are super chewy and come with a great sauce!
Great food!

A small eatery tucked just under the Granville Red line stop, this place is a hidden treasure! Though it is a little pricey, it is an amazing Korean restaurant. WAY better than Bop-N-Grill, though no burgers will be found at Dak. The Spicy BBQ wings were sticky and delectable, and the Spicy Pork Rice Bowl was well balance, savory, and filling.  Pro tip: The wings are WHOLE chicken wings, not individual flats and drummettes. So an order of 5 wings is enough for most individuals. I shared my order and still was satisfied.
This low key joint offers up surprisingly delicious wings. Granville needed a wonderful business like this and I'm glad they're still thriving! Try the dry rub because they're the 💣💣💣
Yummy Dak Sauce on the wings and great BiBimBap! Great place to stop right of the Granville red line!
Just had the wings for the first time today at lunch...They were SO GOOD I'm going back right now to bring some home for dinner!  Wow!
The wings are phenomenal. The spicy BBQ is the better of the two. I didn't like the Beef Entree.
Incredible flavor, friendly service, however the only downside is the decor. The atmosphere could be improved by putting something on the bare grey walls.
Good chicken and bulgogi.

This has been my go-to place for years - to the point that family will visit from out of town and they have to visit every single time they come to Chicago as well. I prefer carry-out to dining in the restaurant - I feel like an old man for saying this, but the music is always too loud. Don't let that deter you... This place is absolutely delicious. I recommend the Spicy BBQ Dak Wings, Rice Bowl with Spicy Pork, Dukbokki with Bulgogi, Egg Rolls - and throw in some waffle fries for good measure. You won't regret anything you get here.

There are two kinds of Korean food: great and mind-blowingly awesome. Dak is the second. Get their doekbokki (dock-bock-e) with waffle fries. I promise you, if you don’t like it, call me up and I’ll come eat it.
Good stuff!

This was my first visit.  The resturant was very clean. The young lady behind the counter was extremely  helpful  and polite. The food is Delicious! ! I will be returning! !! If you are a fan of protein suggest you ask for double. I had the rice bowl spicy pork.

Biggest wings we've ever seen! They were crispy and not drenched in soggy sauce but covered with the perfect amount.  The spicy  chicken rice bowl and bulgogi rice bowl were excellent too! Lots of veggies and a side of red pepper sauce that's addicting. My husband did have a bulgogi as an entree and wasn't  impressed with the portions and lack of veggies but in Daks defense, it never said it came with veggies or additional foods, only rice and steak. Go with rice bowls!
It was amazing! Me and my friends got a Bibimbap and a Dukbokki, the flavors where amazing we loved it. The service was really good too, will definitely come again.
Great food. Better to eat on than take out.  Often gets busy with Loyola students and can be tough to get a table.
Best wings I've ever had! Get the 10 wings spicy and some waffle fries.
Delicious, huge, perfectly fried chicken wings.
The ddeoboki was really really chewy.. my jaws were aching
Wings in Dak sauce are the best. I love this place. Price is about right for a good portion size.

Had I left a review several months ago, I would have given Dak four-stars. However the recent price hike, an encounter with a rude employee, and arbitrary restrictions for side substitutes (side of kimchee==$2 && side of moo==$2, but refusal to swap) changed my mind. The sauces here are good but slightly too sweet, not like real Korean chicken wings...
Great Korean chicken wings!!
A wonderful experience!!!

Really clean place and modern vibe. I tried the chicken wings and they were really good and I loved the "dak" sauce. Great service and I also tried one of their grape juices and it was really good. Super happy with my overall experience.
Wings were delicious!

It's so interesting! I've never been to a restaurant like it before. The chicken wings are HUGE! They're the actual whole wing. The sauces are flavorful and the bowls are full of vegetables. Nothing tastes greasy or frozen. Would recommend!
These are not small wings, though its listed as wings. 5 pieces will fill you up. Good food.
Wings were great. We also ordered a rice bowl and dukbokki. All the sauces were excellent, meats cooked right, and portions well sized. Will be returning/ordering again!

We have tried to go 3 times in the last month for the chicken they are known for.  It is delicious, but all three visits they were out of chicken!!  I can accept that this might happen from time to time, but how do you not know how much you need to meet demand all the time?!? On the this last visit, we even went so far as to call ahead and confirm they had plenty on hand...only to arrive 15 mins later and learn they were out AGAIN! When we protested and reminded them we had just called, they said someone called in an order for 30 PCS.  Really?!?! open for another hour and an order if 30 clears you out?!?
Drove an hour to come to this place to try the Dak Wings, they were crispy and large, best decision ever, will return again!
I like chicken wings there but the source is sometimes too sweet for me.
You NEED to try their Dukbokki!
Wings & rice bowls.
I don't get it why it is so popular on Yelp. But as a Chinese I do not like the sauce here. It's way tooooo sweat.  It's an American Korean restaurant after all.
Consistent and always delicious!
Street parking might be a problem but the taste of wings makes you forgive everything
Waffle fries are literally the best in the city

Full disclosure: I haven't had anything besides the wings at this place besides fries. But honestly, this place has pterodactyl sized wings tossed in flavorful sauces, I don't see why you'd need anything else. The Dak sauce is wonderfully sweet and tangy and the spicy sauce adds a mild kick to that spice, nothing too crazy though. It's all made to order as well, so freshness guaranteed, although that adds around 15 minutes of wait time.  I live in the area, so when I had my uninitiated suburban friends come down, we placed our order and went to Whole Foods to pass time and take advantage of the BYOB policy. That was a fantastic gastronomic experience, although one that my waistline can no longer afford. But for all you youngsters at Loyola and anybody else looking for quality wings, be sure to stop by Dak, you won't be disappointed.
Amazing. Wings are lush
One word: DAK sauce
The wings are truly the star here. Huge, flavorful and crispy and juicy. The service is great and they have some interesting sides if you take a chance.
Delicious, huge chicken wings. But be warned: they are HUGE so the 5 wing order is plenty. It also took 20 minutes for our takeout order to be ready, but it was well worth it.
Some of the best wings you will ever have! The wings here are full size (drumlet + wing) so a 5 piece here is the equivalent of 10 wings at most places.

Wings the size of your head. Sauces that are lip-smackingly delicious. Friendly service in a low-key but super clean and comfy location. We ordered three plates of wings for three people but there was so much food, we probably could have just ordered two.  This place is great. If you're craving delicious Korean BBQ, you won't be disappointed!
Meaty juicy wings.  Love the egg rolls and rice bowls too!
The wings here are fantastic and if you aren't in the mood for wings the rice bowls are excellent as well.

The chicken wings are gigantic and to die for. Either get the spicy or the dak sauce. Their sides and rice dishes are a bit underwhelming as you are better off going to a regular Korean restaurant for that.

The menu is small but very satisfying! At first when I saw the price of 5 wings for $9, I thought it was a ripoff, but these wings are HUGE!!! Very juicy, so much flavor! You just gotta try it! The wings are delicious, but I would recommend trying the Spicy BBQ Pork dinner. It has a hint of spiciness and it is sweet!
Great place for awesome Korean food.
Dukbokki are great, order them with other proteins.
Love the Dak wings and the Beef bowl....

This restaurant is a small little store front, almost didn't see it driving by, it's right next to the red line on Granville.  We got the wings to go, half an hour later the wings were still hit and crunchy. The chicken wings are Hugh, flavorful, and light, how do they make the skin so crunchy and light?, pretty amazing.  We got the dark sauce, it tasted freshly made and on the sweet side like most Korean sauces. Next time will try the spicy version.
Crispy, great flavor
The dukbokki with bulgogi is some of the best I've ever had.
great korean food in chicago
Really good bowls and huge chicken wings. BYOB.  Been here a few times and will be back.
Food taste great and is fresh tasting. Interesting selection of bottle drinks. Try the wings and get a rice bowl both taste great!
Great place in the neighborhood. Fantastic wings! The Bibimbap is delicious too!
Great wings...

I love this place, especially their wings, I would travel across the city to have them if I ever moved away.  Their menu is small but everything on it is so good that it makes up for it.  The place is small and has very limited seating so you may have to wait for a bit if you are wanting to sit down, but rest assured, it is well worth the wait.

Couldn't decide so I got a veggie rice bowl AND chicken wings- SO delicious! Rice bowel was just was I was looking for; healthy veggies and filling! Limited wing sauces, but what they have is so tasty I don't know why you'd want anything else : )
Flip a coin between this and crisp. Worth having if u are nearby.
I think the chicken taste better than the chicken in Korea. The sauce is as good as Korean sauce and the chicken is bigger and soft than Korean chicken. Amazing place!

I love this place for the quality. But korean food is so over priced in Chicago this is ridiculous. You can get same quality food for more in quantity and less if you know the right places. But for this area this is the best you can find! update I tried their fried chicken, and would really like to suggest that with the bbq sauce! It's amazing!
Excellent food.
Really great wings. Order before you get there!
Dukbokki with Bulgogi is my favorite!!
The wings are crispy and delicious

The chicken wings are so worth the price - big and delicious, both BBQ and spicy! I was a bit disappointed to try the classic Korean dishes because they're very Americanized and not the authentic taste I was looking for, although it was still delicious. I love their chalk board menu above the cashier and how they keep it simple.

Definitely the best spot for chicken wings!! And pretty much everything on their menu I'd rate 5 stars. Great food, friendly service, and the Korean family that owns the place, cooks all the food in the back! Seriously, can't go wrong.
It was ALRIGHT and too expensive.
Get the wings!

Just about as good as food gets.  DAK sauce is fragrantly spicy and delicious without obsessive heat.  Do not judge the menu by price alone with 5 wings for 9 bucks, these wings are huge and very meaty and great quality.  So big in fact it make it hard to understand why chickens can't fly.  A must for wings fans, Asian cuisine lover and any kind of foodie.  Also, the battered waffle fries are delish and the serving is huge.
Nice flashback effect. The flavors sent me back to Seoul for a moment. Thanks. Great service, great food. I will be back for sure.

DAK- Chicken wings are HUGE, my goodness!  But man, oh, man are they tasty.  Good crisp on them, and two kinds of flavors: spicy bbq and soy garlic ginger.  I ordered for carry out and they were very accommodating by putting the sauce on the side (spicy bbq), because I like spicy and others at home do not.  I have not tired anything else from Dak, but better believe I will be back! The place is nice and clean and cashiers are very nice.

Dak is a godsend to the far northside.  It's closer to me than the other Korean chicken wing joints (which I think are just as good...there's no discrimination when it comes to Korean wings) and the wings here are HUGE and meaty.  Crispy, crunchity goodness (you can hear the crunch as you chew) on the outside and tender in the inside.  The wings are served hot, like right out of the fryer hot.  It's torture just waiting for the wings to cool off when you're hungry and know how good the wings are.  I'm usually satisfied after three wings since they're so huge.  I've had the wings with both the Dak soy garlic sauce and the spicy BBQ sauce and enjoyed each one.  I've also tried the rice bowl with bulgogi, which is delicious and again, huge.  You will be leaving Dak stuffed!  I plan on returning many times for more wings and to also try Dak's other items.
BEST Korean BBQ wings in town. This place is new and it has definately proven itself. Great service, even better food! The chicken wings are huge and the rice bowls are out of this world.

All I have to say about DAK is 2 words!!! Fricking Amazing! Amazing wings....2 flavors, but still awesome. Spicy Barbeque and Sweet Garlic. Perfect drunk food! They also have rice bowls! which are fresh to death! literally. The food is so fresh. I dont know how original Koreans would feel about the food, but it is great so screw Kim Jung Unn!

My girlfriend and i stumbled upon this place a few nights ago, the wings were sticky, sweet and perfectly fried; super crispy and moist. The veggie bowl was more intense than we expected, in a good way. It was served in a large metal bowl, with rice, noodles, veggies and a fried egg on top, along with some tasty and fiery hot sauce.

I went here randomly because we happened to be at Granville and hungry. Oh my god. It's my new favorite place!!! The chicken wings were perfectly cooked and huge. I thought the $9 was a bit much, but then I ate them I changed my mind. Definitely a fair price. The veggie bowl was equally amazing, which surprised me. I split one order of that and the 5 piece wings and it was perfect for 2 people. We actually had a wing leftover. I HIGHLY recommend this place! The staff is so nice too!

These wings are amazing. Huge, crispy, with unique and delicious sauces. I prefer the spicy ones, but I wouldn't kick the soy sauce ones out of bed either. Not that I eat Dak wings in bed. Or at least I haven't at the time of this posting. But now the idea is in my head. Hmm.  I have been known to eat the extra sauce out of the bottom of the to go container with a spoon. Wait. I've said too much. Forget all that.  Get the wings. Get a lot of wings. The other stuff is okay, but you can get better basic Korean food elsewhere. Go to this place for the wings.  Did I mention the wings?
